A [scheduled Cloud Function deployed with the Firebase CLI][1] will be the proper way to update your data in firebase. Your can run a scheduled function which can be triggered at a specific time (everyday or week however you want) and you can update your variable in the database inside the function. Here is a sample from firebase official documentation : 
```nodejs
exports.scheduledFunctionCrontab = functions.pubsub.schedule(&#39;5 11 * * *&#39;)
  .timeZone(&#39;America/New_York&#39;) // Users can choose timezone - default is America/Los_Angeles
  .onRun((context) =&gt; {
  console.log(&#39;This will be run every day at 11:05 AM Eastern!&#39;);
  return null;
});
```
Read documentation here : https://firebase.google.com/docs/functions/schedule-functions#write_a_scheduled_function


  [1]: https://firebase.google.com/docs/functions/schedule-functions

